    "body": "That's pretty nice.\n\nallCurrentRefinementList => allCurrentRefinement**s**List\n\nWe should focus on the big one (allCurrentRefinemenstList) for 1.0.0.\n\nAlso I would not introduce the clear.after/before notation, like we saw in clearAll discussions (#359) discussions, the easiest way is to create only links and let the theme handle the (x) position with :before/:after.\n\nWDYT?\n",
